commentTextItems.html: miscues the drive off the half volley, takes the outer half of the bat, short cover Sami dives forward and to his right, takes the ball inches off the ground, umpire Sarika Prasad confers with his colleague Buddhi Pradhan at square leg before raising the finger and Afghanistan have won by 70 runs

commentPostTextItems.html: Afghanistan lay the bogeyman to ground, UAE finally beaten by them and it took two terrific innings from Man of the Match Mohammad Nabi and Sami Shenwari to do it. They rescued Afghanistan from 124 for 4 and once he survived a chance when on 16, Nabi went on to make UAE pay. Young Usman Ghani staked his claim for a regular spot in the senior team with another fifty and Noor Ali was his usual immaculate self until getting out. When UAE were batting and Amjad Ali and Khurram Khan were together it looked like they'd at least get close to the target of 302 but Amjad fell for 98 and Khurram soon after and UAE fell away. Two out of two wins for Afghanistan so far, UAE have lost their two. Saturday's a rest day, the ACC Premier League resumes on Sunday. Thank you for being with us.

commentPreTextItems.html: Rahmat Shah changes ends, Mosque End now

dismissalText.long: c Dawlat Zadran b Mohammad Nabi
dismissalText.commentary: Salman Faris c Dawlat Zadran b Mohammad Nabi 27 (46b 3x4 0x6) SR: 58.69

dismissalComment.html: just a bit more loop on that one, lands outside off, takes the thick outside edge as an ambitious drive's attempted and Dawlat at backward point inside the circle clutches the ball chest high coming in

dismissalText.commentary: Shaiman Anwar c & b Amir Hamza 8 (4b 2x4 0x6) SR: 200

dismissalComment.html: beaten in the flight and that's a huge blow, Shaiman Anwar is the UAE's best batsman

dismissalText.commentary: Swapnil Patil b Mirwais Ashraf 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: kept low, ball skidding through and that's a big wicket, Swapnil was the in-form batsman

dismissalText.commentary: Amjad Ali lbw b Rahmat Shah 98 (107b 11x4 1x6) SR: 91.58

dismissalComment.html: plays down the wrong line, and he's out! Spun a couple of inches past the forward defensive bat and that's a huge wicket, a hundred and more looked on for Amjad.

dismissalText.long: c Samiullah Shinwari b Rahmat Shah
dismissalText.commentary: Ahmed Raza c Samiullah Shinwari b Rahmat Shah 2 (12b 0x4 0x6) SR: 16.66

dismissalComment.html: miscues the drive off the half volley, takes the outer half of the bat, short cover Sami dives forward and to his right, takes the ball inches off the ground, umpire Sarika Prasad confers with his colleague Buddhi Pradhan at square leg before raising the finger and Afghanistan have won by 70 runs

milestones.description: Khurram Khan and Amjad Ali's 86-run partnership is UAE's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 82 between Vijay Mehra and Mohammad Ishaq
Mohammad Nabi and Samiullah Shinwari's 125-run partnership is AFG's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 93 between Nawroz Mangal and Asghar Afghan
Amjad Ali has become the top scorer for UAE in ODIs with 228 runs, going past Mazhar Hussain's 179
Amjad Ali has scored 2 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for UAE breaking Swapnil Patil's record
Samiullah Shinwari has scored 6 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for AFG breaking Shahzad's record
Dawlat Zadran has broken the record for most ducks (3) in ODIs for AFG, going past Shapoor's 3
Mohammad Nabi has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (33) for AFG, going past Samiullah Shinwari
